# musclemap-data — Project 1 of 3

## Thesis Pipeline Context

This project is **Project 1** in a 3-project research pipeline:

| Project | Name | Role |
|---|---|---|
| 1 (this) | `musclemap-data` | Motion-X++ SMPL-X motions → muscle activations via OpenSim |
| 2 (future) | `musclemap-model` | Fine-tuned MotionGPT: text → muscle activations |
| 3 (future) | `musclemap-eval` | Benchmark musclemap-model vs Kinesis and original MotionGPT |

**Project 2 loads `output_dataset/` from this project as its training corpus.**
The following output contract must never be broken:

```
output_dataset/
  <sequence_id>/
    activations.npy          # float32, shape [T, N_muscles]
    smplx_322.npy            # float32, shape [T, 322]  (passthrough, unchanged)
    semantic_label.txt       # sequence-level text description
    pose_descriptions/
      <frame_idx>.txt        # one file per frame
  muscle_names.json          # list[str], length == N_muscles
  metadata.json              # dict[id -> {T, fps, source, n_muscles, status}]
```

**Never hardcode N_muscles or fps.** Derive from `muscle_names.json` and `config['output']['output_fps']`.
**activations.npy must always be float32**, not float64.
